---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="Get Involved | RealityFoundation" active="get-involved">
  <div class="pb-8 border-b mb-10" style="border-color: var(--color-line);">
    <p class="mb-3 text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest" style="color: var(--color-muted);">Get Involved</p>
    <h1>Join the effort</h1>
    <p>
      RealityFoundation is a small team with a large research agenda. We need
      collaborators, advisors, and contributors from across academia, industry,
      law, and journalism. Here is how different people can plug in.
    </p>
  </div>

  <!-- Audience cards -->
  <section class="mb-16">
    <div class="grid gap-4" style="grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(min(380px, 100%), 1fr));">
      <div class="border rounded-lg p-8 flex flex-col gap-4" style="border-color: var(--color-line); background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-background-soft) 90%, black 10%);">
        <p class="mb-3 text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest" style="color: var(--color-muted);">For researchers</p>
        <h3>Academic collaboration</h3>
        <p style="color:var(--mono-muted); font-size:var(--text-sm);">
          We are actively seeking co-researchers and advisors across computer
          vision, cryptography, media law, and forensic science. We offer:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Co-authorship on working papers and journal submissions</li>
          <li>Access to the Foundation's datasets and tooling</li>
          <li>Visiting researcher arrangements</li>
          <li>Scientific Committee membership for senior academics</li>
        </ul>
        <a href="mailto:research@realityfoundation.eu" class="btn btn-primary"
          >Contact the research team</a
        >
      </div>

      <div class="border rounded-lg p-8 flex flex-col gap-4" style="border-color: var(--color-line); background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-background-soft) 90%, black 10%);">
        <p class="mb-3 text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest" style="color: var(--color-muted);">For students</p>
        <h3>Thesis & internship</h3>
        <p style="color:var(--mono-muted); font-size:var(--text-sm);">
          We work with MSc and PhD candidates whose dissertations touch on our
          research themes. We can provide:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Supervision co-arrangements with your home institution</li>
          <li>Access to research data and literature resources</li>
          <li>Mentorship from Foundation researchers</li>
          <li>
            A channel to publish thesis-derived work as Foundation outputs
          </li>
        </ul>
        <a href="mailto:students@realityfoundation.eu" class="btn btn-primary"
          >Enquire about student programmes</a
        >
      </div>

      <div class="border rounded-lg p-8 flex flex-col gap-4" style="border-color: var(--color-line); background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-background-soft) 90%, black 10%);">
        <p class="mb-3 text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest" style="color: var(--color-muted);">For policymakers</p>
        <h3>Policy engagement</h3>
        <p style="color:var(--mono-muted); font-size:var(--text-sm);">
          We produce policy-facing outputs and welcome dialogue with regulators,
          legislators, and standards bodies. We can offer:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Policy briefs on specific regulatory questions</li>
          <li>Expert input to consultations and working groups</li>
          <li>Evidence submissions to parliamentary inquiries</li>
          <li>Briefings for parliamentary and regulatory staff</li>
        </ul>
        <a href="mailto:policy@realityfoundation.eu" class="btn btn-primary"
          >Contact the policy team</a
        >
      </div>

      <div class="border rounded-lg p-8 flex flex-col gap-4" style="border-color: var(--color-line); background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-background-soft) 90%, black 10%);">
        <p class="mb-3 text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest" style="color: var(--color-muted);">For journalists</p>
        <h3>Press & media</h3>
        <p style="color:var(--mono-muted); font-size:var(--text-sm);">
          We are available for expert comment, technical explanation, and
          background briefings on synthetic media, deepfakes, and digital
          provenance. We offer:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>On-record expert comment for articles and broadcasts</li>
          <li>Technical explainers for non-specialist audiences</li>
          <li>Fact-checking assistance on specific cases</li>
          <li>Regular press briefings as publications emerge</li>
        </ul>
        <a href="mailto:press@realityfoundation.eu" class="btn btn-primary"
          >Press enquiries</a
        >
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <hr class="border-none border-t my-8" style="border-color: var(--color-line);" />

  <!-- Industry partners -->
  <section class="mb-16">
    <div class="mb-8">
      <h2>Industry & Institutional Partners</h2>
      <p>
        We work with organisations that can contribute data, funding, or domain
        expertise to the research programme — on terms that preserve our
        independence.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="max-w-3xl">
      <p>
        If your organisation handles digital media at scale — insurers, media
        publishers, legal firms, platform operators — you may have datasets or
        operational experience that would advance our research. In return, you
        gain early access to findings, acknowledgement in publications, and the
        ability to shape research questions.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>We do not accept funding that conditions our findings.</strong> All
        partnership terms are published in our annual report. Independence is non-negotiable.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div style="margin-top:var(--space-6)">
      <a href="mailto:partnerships@realityfoundation.eu" class="btn btn-primary"
        >Discuss a partnership</a
      >
    </div>
  </section>

  <hr class="border-none border-t my-8" style="border-color: var(--color-line);" />

  <!-- Newsletter -->
  <section class="mb-16">
    <div class="panel" style="max-width:540px;">
      <p class="mb-3 text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest" style="color: var(--color-muted);">Stay informed</p>
      <h2
        style="font-size:var(--text-lg); letter-spacing:0.04em; text-transform:uppercase; margin-bottom:var(--space-3);"
      >
        Research updates
      </h2>
      <p
        style="color:var(--mono-muted); font-size:var(--text-sm); margin-bottom:var(--space-6);"
      >
        We send infrequent emails when new publications, blog posts, or
        significant research milestones are reached. No noise.
      </p>
      <form
        style="display:flex; gap:var(--space-3); flex-wrap:wrap;"
        onsubmit="handleSignup(event)"
      >
        <input
          type="email"
          placeholder="your@institution.edu"
          required
          style="flex:1; min-width:200px; background:var(--mono-bg); border:1px solid var(--mono-line); border-radius:var(--radius-md); padding:0.55rem 0.9rem; color:var(--mono-text); font-size:var(--text-sm); outline:none;"
          onfocus="this.style.borderColor='#555'"
          onblur="this.style.borderColor='var(--mono-line)'"
        />
        <button type="submit" class="btn btn-primary">Subscribe</button>
      </form>
      <p
        id="signup-msg"
        style="font-size:var(--text-xs); color:var(--mono-muted); margin-top:var(--space-3); display:none;"
      >
        Thanks — we will be in touch when there is something worth reading.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <script>
    function handleSignup(e) {
      e.preventDefault();
      e.target.style.display = "none";
      document.getElementById("signup-msg").style.display = "block";
    }
  </script>
</BaseLayout>
